<HEAD>Bush to Attend Drug Summit Despite Peru's Panama Protest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush still plans to attend a
February drug summit in Colombia even though Peru, the world's
largest cocaine producer, canceled its participation to protest the
U.S. assault on Panama.
   Presidential spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said Thursday that Bush
will still go to Cartagena, Colombia as a show of support for
President Virgilio Barco, whose nation has been at war with drug
