Alex Abdalla Jr., 17, who joined his father, Fetky said.
   As Santos was leaving, Rosado kicked him in the face and Abdalla
Sr. beat him with a metal spring while he lay unconscious on the
ground, Fetky said.
   Abdalla Jr., who was 16 at the time of the August 1988 beating,
pleaded guilty to juvenile delinquency in the case. He was
sentenced Oct. 12 and is serving up to four years in juvenile
custody.
