<HEAD>List of Mail Bomb Incidents</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Judge Explosion</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   The explosion Friday that injured a Maryland judge was the fifth
mail bombing within a week directed at individuals and institutions
in the legal or civil rights arenas. Here is a list:
   DEC. 16 _ Judge Robert S. Vance of the 11th Circuit Court of
Appeals is killed and and his wife seriously injured when a
nail-studded bomb explodes at their home in Birmingham, Ala.
   DEC. 18 _ Parcel bomb is found at the offices of the 11th
Circuit Court of Appeals in Atlanta. The package was defused safely.
   DEC. 18 _ Alderman and civil rights lawyer Robert E. Robertson
is fatally injured when a bomb explodes as he opens a package sent
to his office in Savannah, Ga.
   DEC. 19 _ Another bomb surfaces at the NAACP office in
Jacksonville, Fla. and is removed safely.
   DEC. 22 _ County Circuit Judge John Corderman of Hagerstown, Md.
is injured after a bomb explodes in his apartment 20 minutes after
a package was delivered.
