<FILEID>AP-NR-12-22-89 2144EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>a f BC-MostProfitable-List Adv25   12-22 0425</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Most Profitable-List, Adv 25,0477</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv 25</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Monday Dec. 25</HEAD>
<HEAD>Forbes List of the 50 Most Profitable U.S. Firms of the '80s ^With
BC-Forbes Most Profitable</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is Forbes magazine's list of the 50 most
profitable American firms of the 1980s.
   The list includes, rank, company name, 10-year average return on
equity, latest 12-month return on equity and headquarters city.
   Return on equity expresses profitability as a percentage of the
company's net worth.
   1, Liz Claiborne, 51.8, 32.8, New York.
   2, Rollins, 47.2, 37.8, Atlanta.
   3, Price Co., 40.5, 24.3, San Diego.
   4, Limited, 39.9, 33.0, Columbus, Ohio.
