   Avon, a New York-based cosmetics company, has twice rejected
takeover proposals earlier this year and fended off takeover
feelers from Dallas-based Mary Kay Corp., the privately held parent
of door-to-door marketer Mary Kay Cosmetics.
   A subsidiary of Mary Kay is among the general partners of
Chartwell, which also include the Gordon P. Getty Family Trust and
the Fisher real estate family of New York.
